Site_Comments: Vienyards on one side, spotty crimson clover on other side of the road. Tractor spraying the grape vines was a bit noisy, but this location is one of the furthest north, so did the survey anyways. Top noise levels were from cars going by not the tractor.

one side open field, other side some kind of crop

Purple finch, cedar waxwings, red-breasted nuthatch, California scrub-jay.
Grass fields on the west, ag buildings, grass and hazelnuts on the east. Paved road with busy traffic and fast moving cars.

Several more (3-4) were seen another 1/2 mile or so to the north as I drove out. A well known spot for finding horned larks in Polk County. Wide gravel road.
